extraData.Additional Information: The Gillette Stadium mass vaccination site now has two separate areas for vaccinations located on opposite sides of the arena: Gillette Stadium West and Gillette Stadium East. This is the Gillette Stadium East location. If you have mobility issues, you'll probably find Gillette Stadium West easier to navigate. The distance from the parking lot to the stadium entrance is quite a bit shorter. You may want to consider booking there instead. ***Per the Commonwealth of Massachusetts' vaccine distribution timeline, this clinic is for all Phase 1 priority groups and these Phase 2 priority groups: individuals ages 75+, one companion per 75+ individual (same-day appointment required), individuals ages 65+, individuals ages 16+ with two or more of certain medical conditions, and residents and staff of public and private low-income and affordable senior housing.*** Please arrive just 5 minutes prior to your appointment (not sooner or later), remember to wear a mask, and practice social distancing at all times. You should expect to be at the vaccination site for about 60-75 minutes — from the time you check in until your post-shot observation period ends.

name: Saint Vincent Hospital Vaccine Collaborative @ Worcester State University - Wellness Center

extraData.Additional Information: By Appointment Only - Arrive 15min before schedule appointment. BRING PHOTO ID AND INSURANCE CARDS. PHASE 1 individuals must bring proof of employment (photo ID or paystub). Do not enter the building until 5 min before your scheduled appt time. MASKS are required and must be worn properly at all times. Wear clothing that allows a clinician to easily access your upper arm. The vaccine is delivered to the deltoid muscle, the big muscle on your shoulder. Consider wearing a short-sleeved shirt, or wear a short-sleeved shirt under a sweater or jacket that can be easily removed.

extraData.Additional Information: COVID-19 vaccination clinics at the Worcester Senior Center for persons eligible to receive vaccine in Phase 1 who either live or work in the City of Worcester or the Towns of Grafton, Shrewsbury, Millbury, Holden and West Boylston ONLY. ACCEPTABLE PROOF OF EMPLOYMENT: 1. Copy of Professional License; 2. Work identification badge; 3. Letter from your employer on company letterhead if you are not professionally licensed and do not have a work identification badge. COVID 19 vaccine cannot be administered within 14 days of receipt of another vaccine or within 90 days of receipt of convalescent plasma or monoclonal antibodies. Moderna vaccine is only available as a second dose for those persons who received dose #1 at the 01/25/2021 clinic at the Worcester Senior Center.

***Per the Commonwealth of Massachusetts' vaccine distribution timeline, this clinic is for all Phase 1 priority groups, plus the first and second priority groups in Phase 2. Please arrive only 5 minutes prior to your appointment (not sooner or later) and bring proof of eligibility. Please remember to wear a mask and practice social distancing at all times. You should expect to be at the vaccination site for about 60-75 minutes, all told — from the time you check in until your post-shot observation period ends. There is a 15-minute variance depending on the duration required for your post-shot observation.

name: Needham Public Health - Center at the Heights

extraData.Additional Information: Needham Public Health will hold a clinic only for 18 years and older and for all Phase 1 priority groups and those eligible in Phase 2. Please arrive only 5 minutes prior to your appointment (not sooner or later) and bring proof of eligibility, license and insurance cards. Masks must always be worn. You should expect to be at the vaccination site for about 45-60 minutes, from the time you check in until your post-shot observation period ends. There is a 15-minute variance depending on the duration required for your post-shot observation. **Needham Public Health available clinics are for 1st Vaccine ONLY** If you have received your 1st dose at a different location, we are unable to accommodate you for your second dose at Needham Public Health.
